The **`numtide/llm-agents.nix`** flake provides a collection of Nix packages for various AI coding agents and development tools[1][2][3].

### Using the Packages
You can use the packages directly from the flake without needing an overlay, or by adding it to your flake inputs.

#### 1. Quick Run
To run a tool immediately without installation:
```bash
nix run github:numtide/llm-agents.nix#<package-name> -- --help
```
*(Replace `<package-name>` with tools like `codex`, `qwen-code`, or `zeroclaw`[2].)*

#### 2. Adding to Flake Inputs
To use these tools in your own project or system configuration, add the repository to your `flake.nix`:

```nix
{
  inputs = {
    nixpkgs.url = "github:NixOS/nixpkgs/nixos-unstable";
    llm-agents.url = "github:numtide/llm-agents.nix";
  };

  outputs = { self, nixpkgs, llm-agents }: {
    # Example: Accessing packages in your configuration
    # packages.x86_64-linux.default = llm-agents.packages.x86_64-linux.<package-name>;
  };
}
```

### Overlays
If you wish to use the packages via an overlay (e.g., to make them available in `pkgs`), the flake exposes an overlay that you can import[2][4]. 

Depending on your setup, you can add it to your Nixpkgs configuration:

```nix
nixpkgs = {
  overlays = [
    llm-agents.overlays.default
  ];
};
```

*Note: The packages are built against the flake's pinned `nixpkgs` version to ensure binary cache hits[2]. When using the overlay, ensure your system's `nixpkgs` version is compatible.*

